<emphasis id="CAE67CC98D1F475A620BD8C94D9E5296" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Melinus minutiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="43842ED3F33F7FB17D4FC7FCFE963547" authorityName="Desv" authorityYear="1831" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Microchloa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Microchloa kunthii" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="kunthii">
<emphasis id="ACA8D594A1172C311BD20679EF4AAF44" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Microchloa kunthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Desv., 
<taxonomicName id="B65E20941696FCF6010713899F54C109" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia ciliata" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliata">
<emphasis id="2C858EA91D5FF935F27524E777003A3F" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Muhlenbergia ciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="77B498E2BBBAFF9D84661D1D96D870F5" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName id="9792E39DF5D4E13972860187AEC82D88" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. rigida" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="rigida">M. rigida</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2D64A6FFFF84E65B17449D2A5D3E8F8E" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nassella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Nassella" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="genus">Nassella</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
; 1800-2500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7E456A56CB6EB1DFB206EFC920F0A48E" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="EB514532A3A766AD983561823D5A0CD4" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8AD741951F6504F16334099B28A5D96" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">We honour Dr. Konstantin Romaschenko (born 1969) who accompanied PMP and Robert J. Soreng on the collecting trip in which material of the species was gathered.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8A0DA1DFEF3A883F322B28826BB3755E" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" type="comments">
<paragraph id="15B92C95CEC8A4B003AE35740341400E" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27034DF20513BFF7E568B628236F4340" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName id="7E8667AD35756F29CB370C107C754C66" authorityName="P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia romaschenkoi" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romaschenkoi">
<emphasis id="9B0D5A130204DD99D2A73F9680145BDA" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Muhlenbergia romaschenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from 
<taxonomicName id="8CC156159F151116F1C260FBBA5DF2FD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. microsperma" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="microsperma">
<emphasis id="97F401D992CF3C3B2200B9440392DA67" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. microsperma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having longer acute to acuminate glumes (1-2.8 mm long) and by lacking cleistogamous panicles present in the axils of the lower sheaths. 
<taxonomicName id="3BEFB2F6B441DFFFFE57D310F70E3592" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia tenuifolia" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="0C9A3CAA2B9CDEE8476A93E0896418F1" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Muhlenbergia tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kunth) Kunth, a species ranging from southern Arizona, New Mexico and Texas, U.S.A., throughout 
<normalizedToken id="432D15CC75EF5EBD421B2E75A6A338B2" originalValue="México">Mexico</normalizedToken>
and then again in Venezuela, Bolivia and Argentina, is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="92A7E9F1CA38D60D53718385FF2F6B30" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. romaschenkoi" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="romaschenkoi">
<emphasis id="3E772440066CB469DD551A0613994D75" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. romaschenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in having yellowish anthers 0.9-1.5 mm long (
<bibRefCitation id="8EDA56754F2D2F6574B08F717B658494" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027794" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany Monographs" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="1 - 109" refId="B25" refString="Peterson, PM, Annable, CR, 1991. Systematics of the annual species of Muhlenbergia (Poaceae - Eragrostideae). Systematic Botany Monographs 31: 1 - 109, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25027794" title="Systematics of the annual species of Muhlenbergia (Poaceae - Eragrostideae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25027794" volume="31" year="1991">Peterson and Annable 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="25B3CA8853E52B6DE23FFB2767C5BE77" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B24" refString="Peterson, PM, 2003. 17.33 Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 145-201." title="17.33 Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 145 - 201." year="2003">Peterson 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="44C5920DDAFA656612E7E3C5D854B2C6" author="Peterson, P" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="933 - 1000" refId="B36" refString="Peterson, P, Valdes-Reyna, J, Herrera Arrieta, Y, 2007b. Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae): from northeastern Mexico. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 1: 933 - 1000" title="Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae): from northeastern Mexico." volume="1" year="2007 b">Peterson et al. 2007b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EB7BF49E0B182407EE41039CF0BF89DA" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="21 - 54" refId="B28" refString="Peterson, PM, Giraldo-Canas, D, 2011. Las especies de Muhlenbergia (Poaceae: Chloridoideae) de Argentina. Caldasia 33: 21 - 54" title="Las especies de Muhlenbergia (Poaceae: Chloridoideae) de Argentina." volume="33" year="2011">
Peterson and 
<normalizedToken id="B0C0955D14C56DF40A208F70B03DA526" originalValue="Giraldo-Cañas">Giraldo-Canas</normalizedToken>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7B783108A88F964D129EC88624096D06" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="Caldasia" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B29" refString="Peterson, PM, Giraldo-Canas, D, 2012. Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Zuloaga FO, Rugolo ZE, Anton AMR (Eds) Flora Argentina, Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Vol. 3, Tomo 1, Monocotyledoneae, Poaceae: Aristidoideae a Pharoideae. IBODA-IMBIV, CONICET, Buenos Aires, Argentina, 140-154." title="Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Zuloaga FO, Rugolo ZE, Anton AMR (Eds) Flora Argentina, Flora Vascular de la Republica Argentina, Vol. 3, Tomo 1, Monocotyledoneae, Poaceae: Aristidoideae a Pharoideae. IBODA-IMBIV, CONICET, Buenos Aires, Argentina, 140 - 154." year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
). Initially we thought the new species was 
<taxonomicName id="28F309DB4064598E89AEC6D25E90BE9E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. tenuiofolia" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tenuiofolia">
<emphasis id="9960D47272723EAAC7DD69C829BF72AB" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. tenuiofolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with immature anthers 0.3-0.4 mm long. However, our collection of 
<taxonomicName id="7D6846E9B9F98EE294F1E7739F950155" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. romaschenkoi" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="romaschenkoi">
<emphasis id="C79CE9731B8A60AA565E2F8A8AE276DB" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. romaschenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes well-developed florets with mature caryopses and anthers. Therefore, the observed small anthers in 
<taxonomicName id="0E5F76D7B9BEB39360F95E4DDACFC76D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. romaschenkoi" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="romaschenkoi">
<emphasis id="BF129C8285D64FBD8B4A4313ABA8455E" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. romaschenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not a result of immaturity but represent a genetic difference, from 
<taxonomicName id="69362EC3EF651A66B44495C4286F6EA3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. tenuifolia" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="AE5B7CE2ABF2DF2EEEDAFE6DBB4519E1" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is not known in Peru.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="38598FB83BED989FEE369A56BDA180A2" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">
<taxonomicName id="1C7328937EB7DBB6E09980ECE4DD0C86" authorityName="P. M. Peterson" authorityYear="2018" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia romaschenkoi" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="romaschenkoi">
<emphasis id="63F274FE535ECD2FFDACE881E0EB9E7D" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Muhlenbergia romaschenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a member of 
<taxonomicName id="63058CF4E7A854A7145540B3118AF69C" authority="subg. Muhlenbergia" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Muhlenbergia">M. subg. Muhlenbergia</taxonomicName>
, is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="1ABFE443DC6335FE1642A501CE056104" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. spiciformis" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="spiciformis">
<emphasis id="E09431C50A13E2D4BF1F094DAABF2011" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. spiciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Trin. (plastid marker), a species known from south-western United States and throughout Mexico whereas ITS marker aligns it within the 
<taxonomicName id="305E540DCE8E103F4FEC44C085E6DE23" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. tenuifolia" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis id="FB0652E556CF8C73DB01AFDECACEF5E5" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E2A13AB8336D92C7F3E2CE78D0196F20" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A, B Maximum-likelihood tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in red occur in South America; scale bar = 2 %." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/254042" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">1B</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="7F8C63BDB6F9BF55E877DDC68D4953B2" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia spiciformis" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spiciformis">
<emphasis id="F3894C06AE8C3122501FA14BE71D0731" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Muhlenbergia spiciformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the new species in having shorter glumes 0.3-1 mm long and larger anthers 0.9-1.6 mm long (
<bibRefCitation id="E8D5D593235CF3A55B3EB3D0B143586A" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B24" refString="Peterson, PM, 2003. 17.33 Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 145-201." title="17.33 Muhlenbergia Schreb. In: Barkworth ME, Capels KM, Long S, Piep MB (Eds) Magnoliophyta: Commelinidae (in part): Poaceae, part 2 Flora of North America North of Mexico, Vol 25. Oxford University Press, New York, 145 - 201." year="2003">Peterson 2003</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="AC2A4D65B6C5C7A002AC090AE5F99F77" author="Peterson, P" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="933 - 1000" refId="B36" refString="Peterson, P, Valdes-Reyna, J, Herrera Arrieta, Y, 2007b. Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae): from northeastern Mexico. Journal of the Botanical Research Institute of Texas 1: 933 - 1000" title="Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae): from northeastern Mexico." volume="1" year="2007 b">Peterson et al. 2007b</bibRefCitation>
). These results suggest multiple origins for 
<taxonomicName id="8B1F9C0A7A410F12CCF1F390BD0C8539" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. romaschenkoi" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="romaschenkoi">
<emphasis id="51D06C3024CF54BDD3B72384F8BC40FC" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. romaschenkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from North and South American progenitors. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="8BDA513E9E293EA6403B4107F48D8841" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. caxamarcenis" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="caxamarcenis">
<emphasis id="8430525DC7E717F59FB8B5F5A310F79E" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">M. caxamarcenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this scenario appears to be a common pattern of speciation for South American species of 
<taxonomicName id="2B777E27C6D483A4024BD6763659643E" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia" order="Poales" pageId="56" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="51BDE48BB058FA64E69D3EE8C20E7E97" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="179">Muhlenbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, needing further study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
